label: FaCoS
info:
FaCoS


This will let iTrain connect and find one sensor in the 26 type with id 200 range.

The goal is to take MQTT break beam sensors near the end of my tracks and along certain segments to create animations. One idea I have is a tree falls across the tracks with a servo, I can trigger this randomly as long as the break beam hasnt triggered in 30 seconds. Then fake a trigger of that sensor to iTrain doesnt send a train there. Let's see if I can make it work!

name: get(1,info)
func:
msg.payload = '<REPLY get(1,info)>\n' + 
'1 ECoS\n' + 
'1 ProtocolVersion[0.999]\n' + 
'1 ApplicationVersion[1.1.1]\n' + 
'1 HardwareVersion[1.3]\n' + 
'<END 0 (OK)>\n';
return msg;

name: get(200,railcom[0])

get(1000,addr,protocol,symbol,speedindicator)

+'1000 symbol[LOCO_TYPE_E, IMAGE_TYPE_INT, 050]\n'
+'<END 0 (OK)>\n';
